I"‰<p>The greatest storm in living memory blasts the English coast. Striving against the howling winds and pounding waves, a lonely boat struggles on. Those left behind wait impatiently, huddled together, isolated and unfamiliar.</p>

<p>As the storm rages, stories, memories, songs and myths tumble out of the night, capturing a life lived on and around the sea.</p>

<p>Peril at Sea is produced by Up The Road Theatre in association with New Theatre Royal Portsmouth, supported by Wells Maltings, The Seagull and LV21.</p>

<p>Supported by Arts Council England and The Leche Trust.</p>

